  [tr]
  * $keyseq($key(Alt)$key(F6))
  * Cycle through windows in the same application. Hold down the
    $key(Alt) key and press $key(F6) until the window you want is
    highlighted, then release $key(Alt). This is similar to the
    $keyseq($key(Alt)$key(`)) feature.

  [tr]
  * $keyseq($key(Alt)$key(Esc))
  * Cycle through all open windows on a workspace.

  [tr]
  * $keyseq($key(Super)$key(M))
  * $link[>shell-notifications#messagetray](Open the message
    tray.) Press $key(Esc) to close.

[table frame="top bottom" rules="rows"]
  . Navigate windows

  [tr]
  * $keyseq($key(Alt)$key(F4))
  * Close the current window.

  [tr]
  * $keyseq($key(Alt)$key(F5)) or $keyseq($key(Super)$key($2193;))
  * Restore a maximized window to its original size. Use
    $keyseq($key(Alt)$key(F10)) to maximize.
    $keyseq($key(Alt)$key(F10)) both maximizes and
    restores.

  [tr]
  * $keyseq($key(Alt)$key(F7))
  * Move the current window. Press
    $keyseq($key(Alt)$key(F7)), then use the arrow keys to
    move the window. Press $key(Enter) to finish moving the window, or
    $key(Esc) to return it to its original place.

  [tr]
  * $keyseq($key(Alt)$key(F8))
  * Resize the current window. Press
    $keyseq($key(Alt)$key(F8)), then use the arrow keys to
    resize the window. Press $key(Enter) to finish resizing the window, or
    $key(Esc) to return it to its original size.

  [include xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
           href="shell-keyboard-shortcuts.page"
           xpointer="super-shift-updown"]

  [include xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
           href="shell-keyboard-shortcuts.page"
           xpointer="super-shift-left"]

  [include xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
           href="shell-keyboard-shortcuts.page"
           xpointer="super-shift-right"]

  [tr]
  * $keyseq($key(Alt)$key(F10)) or $keyseq($key(Super)$key($2191;))
  * $link [>shell-windows-maximize](Maximize) a window. Press
    $keyseq($key(Alt)$key(F10)) or $keyseq($key(Super)$key($2193;))
    to restore a maximized window to its original size.

  [tr]
  * $keyseq($key(Super)$key(H))
  * Minimize a window.

  [tr]
  * $keyseq($key(Super)$key($2190;))
  * Maximize a window vertically along the left side of the screen.
    Press again to restore the window to its previous size. Press
    $keyseq($key(Super)$key($2192;)) to switch
    sides.

  [tr]
  * $keyseq($key(Super)$key($2192;))
  * Maximize a window vertically along the right side of the screen.
    Press again to restore the window to its previous size. Press
    $keyseq($key(Super)$key($2190;)) to
    switch sides.

  [tr]
  * $keyseq($key(Alt)$key(Space))
  * Pop up the window menu, as if you had right-clicked on the
    titlebar.
